The boundary conditions on the Surfaces, on the Lines, on the Points in 3d,
or on Lines, on Points in 2d, of the FLUID may be defined here.

1 : BOUNDARY EXTERNAL FORCE Density on SL
2 : BLOCKING-UP the IMPOSED VELOCITY on SLP
3 : BLOCKING-UP the IMPOSED PRESSURE on SLP

4 : INITIAL VELOCITIES on SLP
5 : INITIAL PRESSURES on SLP
For the unsteady problem, the INITIAL velocities or/and pressures may be defined from
- the last computed velocities_pressures;
- the constant values or functions on the objet (the fluid)
- the constant values or functions on the VSLP (the volumes, surfaces, lines or points
  of the fluid)
with a priority to the Points, then after, the lines, then after the surfaces,
then after the volumes and finally, the object.

Type @; or escape to quit the actual Surface or Line or Point and to pass to the next.

Attention:
A given boundary or initial condition is always stored.
If this value must not used after, it is necessary to delete it!
If not this value will be used in the next computation.